IEQ_Furn_Section Notes: Most furniture is tablet arm chairs.  Standard tables and chairs in art, media center, and other special spaces.
Instructional_Regular_Section Notes: 700 sf (25 x 28) typical classroomm size. Slide bolts and padlocks typical on doors.  4" Steps to keep water out from walkways into classrooms not accessible.  One marker board and one tack board per room.minimal storage in wall cabinets .
Instructional_SPED_Section Notes: One sped classroom with one marker board and tack board .  One projector  in media center only. Minimal storag in base cabinets..
Instructional_SciAPLCTE_Section Notes: Science, sinks, tables, chairs.w storage room. One marker board.  Computer room classroom size. With plenty power and data.  Accessibility bad as per typical classrooms.
Admin&Health_Section Notes: Reception/waiting room. Four offices, one large double office, two toilets, storage room. No health office or conf room.  Suite entry door has  gates and padlocks.  All doors on campus typically residential storm doors to keep a/c in plus a steel plate door for security.
Public_Section Notes: 700 sf Theater room plus 12' deep raised platform being used for another art room.  Cafeteria is 1036 sf (37 x 28)  No adjacencies. Hardware all slide bolts and 4" steps at entries as is typical. Cafe storage 1400 sf (50 x 28).  Jalosie louvers w screens. No gym, but 60 x 90 covered BB court w three small concrete bleachers seating 60 people total. Media center has some student computers 1736 sf (62 x 28); plus 3 offices and storage room , no other power, tech.  Theater has a stage classroom size plus 12' deep stage.  Used as classroom
Instructional_Visual&Fitness_Section Not: Art classroom typ classroom size. No sinks one marker board, minimal storage.
Security_Section Notes: Canopy adjacent to drop off. No bus. Unprotected path to parking around side of bldg. No sight  line. Tight site abuts a highway  4' - 6' chain link fence around site, interrupted by jungle in back. Not secure.  Typical gates at front entry.   Much display in entry breezeway.  Site is in a very low area below the hwy retaining wall, and in a wooded area.  Feels secluded.  Stairways are 5'-8" wide.  Walkways are 6' wide.

LearningCommArea_Section Notes: Covered BB court 60 x 100, plus covered bleachers 10 rows x 100' and raised platform area for presentation
EduIEQ_Section Notes: Gates at doors with slide bolts, most have 1 to 2" steps - non-accessible. Some murals
IEQ_Furn_Section Notes: Tablet arm chairs.  Stairs 42".  Computer tables in computer lab.  No ramps  to 3rd and 4th levels.
Instructional_Regular_Section Notes: Typical classroom 24 x26, 1 marker board,  one wall/base cabinet, portable teacher storage.  Metal jalosie louvers each side of classrooms. Tow each One story classroom buildings: 6; classrooms total at  25 x25,: no threshold issues, two marker boards,
Instructional_SPED_Section Notes: 2 SPED suites:;16 x 20 classroom plus toilet, two marker boards ,and 8' x 26' office. 4 standard classrooms.
Instructional_SciAPLCTE_Section Notes: One Science lab, 22 x 38, no sink. Just portable teacher cabinet.  Waiting for more equipment to use it for science.  3d printer.  Computer lab classroom size, one markerboard. Teacher cabinet.
Admin&Health_Section Notes: Combined Reception, secretary and waiting area, director office with toilet, secretary office, conference room with copy, breakroom, toilets .  No health office.
Public_Section Notes: Media center 24 x 80, with computers and smart TV.  No support space. Cafeteria 26 x 64. No servery. Kitchen 15 x 30, storage 15 x 18 and 12 x 20.
Instructional_Visual&Fitness_Section Not: music room 25 x  20, with two marker boards. Art classroom 20 x 32, with sink, two marker boards.  Teacher cabinet
Security_Section Notes: Perimeter fence 6' concrete fencing, iron fence in front, but openings for driveway and broken down spot.. Covered parking around side of campus. No sight lines parking.

LearningCommArea_Section Notes: Covered outdoor BB court appears to be the central public/gathering/activity area.  It was very much in use after school as well.  Circulation: 6' walkways and overhangs.  Three small fenced outdoor play areas with minimal play equipment and no safety cushioned tiles, adjacent to lower grade level classrooms.
EduIEQ_Section Notes: 18 mo - 3 year olds.  Small tables and chairs..  sink, little storage, non acoustical layin panels. Campus style configuration.  No sound transmission between rooms generally due to concrete walls, but concrete surfaces in rooms don't absorb sound. Doors are the double storm doors and steel plate doors with slide bolts, and 2" steps to keep water out, so non accessible.
IEQ_Furn_Section Notes: Differentiated tables but standard chairs.  No markerboards since it is Montessori-method of teaching.
Instructional_Regular_Section Notes: One-story building classrooms 621 sf (27 x 23): and interconnecting doorways.  Several isolated classroom buildings.  3-6 grade classrooms 912 sf (24 x 38), with sinks, toilet room, storage room, each room.  2-story building classrooms 660 sf (22 x 30).
Instructional_SPED_Section Notes: No sped classrooms. SPED kids are all in with others.  Therapist works with individuals.
Instructional_SciAPLCTE_Section Notes: No learning areas of these types.
Admin&Health_Section Notes: Director, secretary  breakroom w solar system equipment. Tiny waiting area in small entry corridor. Health office remote in building   Health has sink and therapy and used for SPED . size462 sf ( 21 x 2).  No ground level rooms accessible due to the 2" high steps at entries to keep water out, and gates with doors with slide bolts.
Public_Section Notes: Media center being used as storage 621 sf (23 x 27). Jalosie  louver openings typically. All doors with gates and solid doors with slide bolts. Not accessible  2" steps at entries to keep water out. Covered outdoor BB court  5400 sf (60' x 90') with one 3-tier by 16' tip-and-roll bleacher unit, and single bench seating. Cafeteria 1100 sf (50' x 22') including the kitchen equipment.  Good standard tables and chairs.  4 shifts served, but also includes BB court for capacity. Also has storage (locked) and toilet for staff.
Instructional_Visual&Fitness_Section Not: Art room 368 sf (16 x 23).  Standard tables and chairs.
Security_Section Notes: Front entry faces street, parking is inside courtyard between buildings, so no sight line, and accessed from side street.  Community engagement with displays and  murals, and the tight cramped spaces seemed to increase connections.
